    <div class="body">
        <p>It's strange, isn't it?</p>

<p>abstract class Zend_Db_Table {
    ...
    static protected $_inflector;
    ...
    public function __construct($config = null)
    {
        ...
        self::$_inflector = new Zend_Db_Inflector();
        ...
    }</p>

<p>Everytimes when we create a new table descendent instance, new Inflector will create and replace old one.</p>

<p>Question #2: Why Inflector is not a static object? It isn't consist any properties.</p>

<p>I don't understand this things.</p>

